OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777169008
OL,3,CQueen to give replacement Roo to
OL,4,Ccomplete US library's Winnie-the-Pooh
OL,5,Ctoy set
OL,7,FThis is home to the teddy bears which
OL,8,Fbelonged to Christopher Robin, son of
OL,9,FWinnie-the-Pooh creator A A Milne, and
OL,10,Fwhich are believed to have inspired
OL,11,Fthe stories first published a century
OL,12,Fago in 1926.
OL,14,FThe collection on display includes
OL,15,FWinnie, Tigger, Piglet, Kanga and
OL,16,FEeyore but is missing the original
OL,17,Fbaby kangaroo toy ` Roo ` which was
OL,18,Flost in an apple orchard in the 1930s.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
